By Adeboye Amosu:                              Super Eagles defender Shehu Abdullahi hopes to see his Turkish Super League club, Bursaspor win their final home game of the season against Trabzonspor, Completesportsnigeria. com reports. Bursaspor will host Trabzonspor  today (Sunday) at the Buyuksehir Belediye Stadium. “Let’s finish the season strong! Last Home Game.. We are @BursasporSk !!! ,” he wrote on his Twitter handle. Their last  game of the season is at  Gençlerbirliği next weekend. Bursaspor sit in 11th position in the table with 39 points from 32 games. Abdullahi only joined Bursaspor from Cypriot club, Anorthosis Famagusta in January. He has made 13 league appearances for the club since the switch. Two other Nigerians, William Troost-Ekong and Mikel Agu are also at the club. The post Abdullahi Targets Win In Bursaspor’s Last Home Game Of Season appeared first on Complete Sports Nigeria.   Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from Complete Sports Nigeria. Click here to read the full text on the original website.